  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "I'm testing dynamic provisioning on AWS. When I create a claim with `volume.alpha.kubernetes.io/storage-class` annotation, Kubernetes creates a PV, marks it as Bound, while the claim is still `Pending`. The claim gets `Bound` only after 10 minutes, i.e. on the next provisioner controller refresh.\n\nWhen the provisioning is complete, the claim should be marked as Bound immediately, probably somewhere at this place: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/controller/persistentvolume/persistentvolume_provisioner_controller.go#L294\n",
